      "writtenOn": "2026-03-03T13:02:40Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This approach has a couple of issues:\n- it introduces global state on this singleton\n- this state is gone when the pod is restarted\n- the `volatile String soProcessInstanceId` is detrimental for performance since only one process at a time may read and modify it\n- you do not have any cleanup logic in place it seems, so this will basically result in a memory leak with a sufficient number of process executions\n(since this hashmap can only group)\n\nFor all these reasons this approach should be changed to rely on persistence (in the request-db for instance) since that is where request related information is already stored if I understand the SO architecture correctly",
